---
import LegalLayout from '../components/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Luminate Energy"
  description="How Luminate Energy LLC collects, uses, and protects information about visitors and customers of luminate.solar."
  eyebrow="Privacy"
  eyebrowNumber="01"
  heading="Privacy"
  headingAccent="policy."
  lastUpdated="May 21, 2026"
>
  <p>
    Luminate Energy LLC ("Luminate," "we," "us," or "our") respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy
    explains what information we collect from visitors and customers of <strong>luminate.solar</strong>,
    how we use it, and the choices you have. By using this website or contacting us, you agree to the
    terms of this policy.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Information we collect</h2>
  <p>We collect information in two ways:</p>
  <h3>Information you provide</h3>
  <p>
    When you submit our contact form, request a quote, or otherwise reach out to us, you may give us:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Name</li>
    <li>Email address</li>
    <li>Phone number</li>
    <li>Home or property address</li>
    <li>Information about your energy usage, roof, or solar interest (e.g., bill amount, roof age)</li>
    <li>Any other details you choose to share in the message field</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Information collected automatically</h3>
  <p>
    Our website and hosting provider may automatically collect limited technical information such as
    your IP address, browser type, device type, referring URL, and pages visited. We use this to
    understand site performance and to protect against abuse. We do not use third-party advertising
    or cross-site tracking on this website.
  </p>

  <h2>2. How we use your information</h2>
  <p>We use the information you provide to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Respond to your inquiry and follow up on a consultation or quote</li>
    <li>Schedule on-site assessments and prepare system designs</li>
    <li>Communicate about the status of your project, installation, or service</li>
    <li>Send service-related updates and warranty information</li>
    <li>Improve our website, services, and customer experience</li>
    <li>Comply with legal obligations and protect our rights</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. How we share your information</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>We do not sell your personal information.</strong> We share information only with the
    parties needed to deliver the services you request, including:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Equipment manufacturers and distributors involved in your specific project</li>
    <li>Licensed installation crews, electricians, and roofers we work with</li>
    <li>Permitting authorities, utility companies, and finance partners (only when needed for your project, and only with your knowledge)</li>
    <li>Service providers that help us operate the business (e.g., email, form processing, hosting, CRM)</li>
    <li>Law enforcement or other parties when required by law or to protect rights and safety</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    These third parties are expected to safeguard your information and use it only for the purpose
    we share it with them.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Cookies and analytics</h2>
  <p>
    Our website uses minimal cookies. We may use privacy-friendly analytics to measure aggregate
    traffic patterns (such as how many people visit each page) without identifying individual
    visitors. You can disable cookies in your browser settings; the site will still work.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Data retention</h2>
  <p>
    We retain the information you provide for as long as needed to fulfill the purposes described
    above — including responding to your inquiry, completing a project, providing warranty support,
    and complying with tax, accounting, and legal requirements. When that purpose ends, we delete or
    anonymize the information within a reasonable timeframe.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Your choices and rights</h2>
  <p>You can:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Ask us what information we have about you</li>
    <li>Request that we correct or update it</li>
    <li>Request that we delete it (subject to legal and contractual obligations)</li>
    <li>Unsubscribe from marketing communications at any time by replying to any email or contacting us</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    To exercise any of these rights, email us at <a href="mailto:support@luminate.solar">support@luminate.solar</a>.
    We'll respond within a reasonable time.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Children's privacy</h2>
  <p>
    This website is intended for adults. We do not knowingly collect information from children under
    13. If you believe a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us and we
    will delete it.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Security</h2>
  <p>
    We take reasonable steps to protect the information you give us — using encryption in transit
    (HTTPS), access controls, and trusted service providers. No method of internet transmission or
    electronic storage is 100% secure, however, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy from time to time. When we do, we'll change the "Last updated" date at
    the top of this page. If the changes are material, we'll do our best to notify you through the
    site or by email.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Contact us</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about this Privacy Policy? Reach out:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Email: <a href="mailto:support@luminate.solar">support@luminate.solar</a></li>
    <li>Mail: Luminate Energy LLC, Texas, USA</li>
  </ul>
</LegalLayout>
